---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import SheetEmbed from '../components/SheetEmbed.astro';

const fordSrc =
  "https://1drv.ms/x/c/1ab10ce1b91949c7/IQSfbkaNrLC9Q4gMSuvRxNr_AdZuC4Ru8pcFK8ov2DKisTw?em=2&AllowTyping=True&ActiveCell='Ford%20Financial%20Model%202022-2030'!B2&wdHideGridlines=True&wdHideHeaders=True&wdDownloadButton=True&wdInConfigurator=True&wdInConfigurator=True&edaebf=rslc0";
---

<Base
  title="Denise Lin: Ford Motor Co. Financial Forecast Model"
  description="Denise Lin — a live, interactive Ford Motor Co. financial forecast model (2022–2030), built for a Financial Information Analysis class."
>
  <header class="hero wrap wrap--wide">
    <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--gold">Financial Forecasting</p>
    <h1 class="hero__name">Denise Lin</h1>
    <hr class="tick" />
  </header>

  <section class="wrap wrap--wide portfolio" aria-labelledby="port-h">
    <h2 id="port-h" class="portfolio__h">
      Ford Motor Co.: Financial Forecast Model, 2022&ndash;2030
    </h2>
    <p class="portfolio__intro">
      This is a model I built for Ford Motor Co. for my Financial Information
      Analysis class. It&rsquo;s interactive, with the dark blue font
      indicating hardcoded cells that change the model. Feel free to change
      assumptions and see how the model responds.
    </p>

    <div class="spotlight spotlight--hero">
      <div class="spotlight__copy">
        <h3 class="spotlight__h">A forecast is only as good as its assumptions</h3>
        <p>
          Automotive manufacturing is very expensive, and Cost of Goods Sold as a
          percentage of revenue is the critical assumption. Historical COGS / %
          Revenue has ranged from 86&ndash;88% in the past few years.
        </p>
        <blockquote class="pull">
          &ldquo;Consensus sat at 77% for the 2026 forecast, but this seemed way
          too optimistic for me; I selected 85% to consider the efforts
          management is making in increasing efficiencies, without falling too
          much outside of the demonstrated historical range.&rdquo;
        </blockquote>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat__pair">
            <span class="stat__num">~$14B</span>
            <span class="stat__lbl">My 2026 EBITDA, at 85% COGS</span>
          </div>
          <span class="stat__vs" aria-hidden="true">vs.</span>
          <div class="stat__pair stat__pair--muted">
            <span class="stat__num">$29B</span>
            <span class="stat__lbl">The street, at 77% COGS</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>
          The street number would have landed at $29 billion, which is not
          really justifiable, as it is almost 3.5&times; the previous
          year&rsquo;s EBITDA. The active cell below holds that COGS assumption;
          change it and watch EBITDA move.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="spotlight__embed">
        <SheetEmbed
          hero={true}
          height={600}
          src={fordSrc}
          title="Ford Motor Co. financial forecast model, 2022–2030, built by Denise Lin"
          caption="Live model: Ford Motor Co. financial forecast, 2022–2030"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="aside">
      Finding the right inputs was its own challenge: different companies present
      financial statements differently. In Ford&rsquo;s case, multiple items were
      bundled in the SG&amp;A line of the income statement provided by Factset, so
      I downloaded Ford&rsquo;s 10-K to find the correct line items for the
      analysis.
    </p>
  </section>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <div class="wrap wrap--wide">
      <p class="contact">
        <a href="mailto:deniselihanlin@gmail.com">deniselihanlin@gmail.com</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true" class="dot">&middot;</span>
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/denise-lin"
          rel="me noopener"
          target="_blank">LinkedIn</a
        >
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-top: clamp(3.5rem, 10vw, 6.5rem);
    padding-bottom: clamp(0.25rem, 1.2vw, 0.6rem);
  }
  .hero__name {
    font-size: var(--step-3);
  }
  .hero__lede {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1rem + 0.35vw, 1.22rem);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 70ch;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .portfolio {
    padding-block: clamp(0.75rem, 2vw, 1.25rem) clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
  }
  .portfolio__h {
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    max-width: none;
  }
  .portfolio__intro {
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 82ch;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .spotlight {
    padding: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 1.6rem;
  }
  .spotlight--hero {
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--california-gold);
  }
  .spotlight__copy > :first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .spotlight__copy p {
    max-width: 82ch;
  }
  .spotlight__h {
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    color: var(--berkeley-blue);
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }
  .spotlight__embed {
    margin-top: 1.6rem;
  }

  .pull {
    margin: 1.3rem 0;
    padding: 0 0 0 1.2rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--berkeley-blue);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--berkeley-blue);
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .stat {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.8rem 1.4rem;
    margin: 1.4rem 0;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: 8px;
    max-width: 46rem;
  }
  .stat__pair {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }
  .stat__num {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--berkeley-blue);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
  .stat__pair--muted .stat__num {
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .stat__lbl {
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .stat__vs {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--gold-deep);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
  }

  .aside {
    margin: 0 0 1.6rem;
    padding: 0 clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    max-width: none;
  }
</style>
